	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, basically, I <em>never</em> could interface the Allegro' sound in my emulator "error-free". It's not an easy task and I even couldn't take the "risk" of trying Allegro 5. 
<br />
<br />Regarding the samples, well... as far as I know of it, you would need to generate 1 sample at every CPU clock cycle. That means a resample to the PC frequency. I add all the samples and divide by the number of updates. Using Allegro, the amount of samples is always the same; so, you would feed the buffer with, let's say, 2048 samples per sound sync.

		

